member.summary:
Use this object for configure Consent flow dialogs for GDPR. Create and attach the object to CAS initialization.
MobileAds.BuildManager() .WithConsentFlow(new ConsentFlow() .WithPrivacyPolicy("https://url_to_privacy_policy") ) .Initialize();
By default, the consent flow will be shown to users who are protected by laws. You can prevent us from showing the consent dialog to the user ussing followed lines:
MobileAds.BuildManager() .WithConsentFlow(new ConsentFlow(isEnabled: false)) .Initialize();

             Audiences under the age of 13 who subject of COPPA.


When using this feature, a Tag For Users under the Age of Consent in Europe (TFUA) parameter
             will be included in the ad request.
             Also the state of GDPR and CCPA will be overridden automatically
